Margaret C. (Meg) Whitman 

		
		President and CEO, 

	
		 Hewlett Packard Enterprise Company 	

 
Last Updated: 06/07/2017 



Executive Summary
A product of Princeton and Harvard, Whitman spent her early career working at brand behemoths such as Procter & Gamble and Disney, as well as consultancy Bain & Company. In 1998 she jumped on the dot com bandwagon, taking the helm at eBay, which at the time had only 30 employees. She was an Internet darling for nearly a decade& 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Colleagues find Whitman to be hard working, dedicated, consistently upbeat, and relentlessly optimistic. She is said to be open to advice, criticism, and opportunity.
An avid swimmer, Whitman also enjoys fly-fishing, skiing, te 
Current Focus

Three main ways to drive success: In June 2017, Whitman said that the company's shopping spree may not be over. “I think you will see acquisitions become a bigger part of our strategy,” she added. Whitma 
Key Challenges

External factors impacting our performance: During the company’s February 2017 earnings call, Whitman said, “…we saw several external factors impacting our performance that will become more challengin 
Biographical Highlights

Born August 4, 1956, in Cold Spring Harbor, New York
Princeton University, BA, 1977; Harvard Business School, MBA, 1979 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Board of Directors, Zipcar, Inc.
Former Member, Board of Directors, Procter & Gamble Company (2003-2008) 
 





