Margaret C. Whitman: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 5:14 AM ET
Technology Hardware, Storage and Peripherals

Company Overview of Hewlett Packard Enterprise Company



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Margaret C. Whitman  CEO & Executive Director, Hewlett Packard Enterprise CompanyAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 11 Board Members in 11 different organizations across 23 different industries.See Board Relationships61$35,564,351As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Ms. Margaret C. Whitman, also known as Meg, has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Hewlett Packard Enterprise Company since October 2014 and also has been its Executive Director since November 1, 2015. Ms. Whitman serves as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Hewlett Packard Global soft PVT Ltd. She has been an Advisor of SurveyMonkey Inc. since May 24, 2017. She served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of HP Inc. (also known as, Hewlett-Packard ... Company) from September 22, 2011 to November 1, 2015. She served as a Strategic Adviser and Partner of Kleiner, Perkins, Caufield & Byers from March 2011 to September 2011. She served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of eBay Inc. from 1998 to November 2007 and served as its Special Advisor. She served as the Chief Executive Officer at eBay EachNet.com Network Information Services (Shanghai) Co., Ltd. and eBay Eachnet Co. Ltd. She Co-Founded Peer News, Inc. From January 1997 to February 1998, she served as a General Manager of the Preschool Division of Hasbro, Inc. From February 1995 to December 1996, she served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Florists' Transworld Delivery, Inc. She held executive-level positions at FTD Group, Inc. (FTD, Inc.). From October 1992 to February 1995, she was employed by The Stride Rite Corporation as the President of Stride Rite Children's Group and Executive Vice President of Product Development, Marketing and Merchandising at Keds Division. From May 1989 to October 1992, Ms. Whitman served as the Senior Vice President of Marketing and The Disney Consumer Products at The Walt Disney Company. Prior to joining Disney, she served as a Vice President at Bain & Company, Inc. for eight years. She began her career at Procter and Gamble in Cincinnati, where she worked in brand management from 1979 to 1981. She has been the Chairman of the Board of HP Inc. (also known as, Hewlett-Packard Company) since July 2014. Ms. Whitman has been a Director of HP Inc. since January 21, 2011, The Nature Conservancy since March 2011, DXC Technology Company since April 1, 2017, ArcSight, Inc. since January 2011 and Zaarly, Inc. since October 2011. She serves as a Director at Bizbuyer.com. and Hewlett-Packard GlobalSoft Private Limited. She has been an Independent Director at The Procter & Gamble Company since February 8, 2011. She serves as Charter Trustee of Princeton University. She serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Rosewood Capital. She served as a Director of The Procter & Gamble Company from January 1, 2003 to December 31, 2008. She served as a Director of Staples, Inc. She served as a Director of SurveyMonkey Inc. from September 10, 2015 to May 24, 2017. She served as a Director of Zipcar, Inc. from February 28, 2011 to March 14, 2013. She served as a Director of eBay Inc. since March 1998 and TradeOut.com since October 1999. She served as a Director of Staples.com. She served as Director of The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. She served as a Director of The Gap, Inc. from September 30, 2003 to May 2006 and DreamWorks Animation SKG Inc. from April 21, 2005 to December 31, 2008. Earlier, from February 1995 to December 1996, She served as a Director at Florists' Transworld Delivery, Inc. She is a Board Member of Teach For America and Summit Public Schools. Fortune ranked Ms. Whitman as one of the 25 “most powerful people in business” in 2004 and 2005, Time named her one of the world's 100 most influential people in 2004 and Worth ranked her number one on its 2002 list of best Chief Executive Officers and Business Week has included her on its list of the 25 most powerful business managers annually since 2000. Business Week listed her on its list of the most powerful business managers every year from 2000 to 2008. Ms. Whitman holds an M.B.A. degree from the Harvard Business School and a B.A. in Economics from Princeton University.Read Full Background




